BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The coordinates of the points are [`[$A]`] and [`[$B]\text{.}`] We apply the rate of change formula:

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\amp\frac{y_2-y_1}{x_2-x_1}\\
\amp= \frac{[$top]}{[$bottom]}\\
\amp= \frac{[$top->reduce]}{[$bottom->reduce]}
\end{aligned}
```]

So the rate of change is [`[$m]\text{.}`]

